<section>
  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    Keyserver tracks software usage on Penn Libraries public computers.
    Events and sessions are captured from Keyserver's raw tables and loaded into Metridoc.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The <strong>Software Usage</strong> page lists all managed products with checkout activity on non-staff computers, including status (Active / Stale / Dormant) based on days since the last checkout.</li>
    <li>The <strong>Stale &amp; Dormant</strong> page surfaces products with no checkout in 90+ days, sorted by most dormant first.</li>
    <li>The <strong>Locations</strong> page shows session heatmaps by hour of day and day of week, broken down by library location.</li>
    <li>The <strong>By School</strong> page shows checkout counts per product per Alma school affiliation.</li>
    <li>The <strong>By User Group</strong> page shows checkout counts per product per Alma user group (e.g. undergraduate, graduate, faculty).</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section>
  <h2>Dashboards</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><%= link_to "Software Usage Profile", keyserver_software_usage_path %></li>
    <li><%= link_to "Stale &amp; Dormant Products".html_safe, keyserver_stale_path %></li>
    <li><%= link_to "Location Usage", keyserver_locations_path %></li>
    <li><%= link_to "By School", keyserver_by_school_path %></li>
    <li><%= link_to "By User Group", keyserver_by_user_group_path %></li>
  </ul>
</section>

<hr>

<section>
  <h2>Data Import</h2>
  <p>
    To load data, export <code>events.xlsx</code> and <code>sessions.xlsx</code> from itam_db into <code>/tmp/keyserver/</code>,
    then run:
  </p>
  <pre>rake import -- --config_folder keyserver</pre>
</section>
